Source: rauc
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Michael Heimpold <mhei@heimpold.de>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 9), dh-autoreconf, pkg-config, libtool, libglib2.0-dev, libcurl3-dev, libssl-dev, libjson-glib-dev, zlib1g-dev
Standards-Version: 3.9.7
Homepage: https://github.com/rauc/rauc

Package: rauc
Architecture: any
Depends: dbus, squashfs-tools, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Safe and secure software updates for embedded Linux
 RAUC is a lightweight update client that runs on your Embedded Linux device
 and reliably controls the procedure of updating your device with a new
 firmware revision. RAUC is also the tool on your host system that lets you
 create, inspect and modify update artifacts for your device.
